      "description": "Turn the expanded support matrix into sustainable verification. Update default and opt-in gates so future upstream changes cannot silently desynchronize the wrapper, docs, prompt guidance, package doctor, real-upstream contract fixture, or packaged Pi smoke tests. Acceptance criteria: `npm run verify` checks generated docs/playbook drift, typecheck, unit/fake tests, and command-reference baseline; `npm run verify -- real-upstream` covers the expanded safe real-browser matrix; `npm run verify -- package-pi` still loads the package with a fake upstream; doctor reports version drift with clear re-baselining instructions; all scripts have useful help where user-facing; tests are documented in release docs.",
      "priority": "high",
      "tags": [
        "verification",
        "ci",
        "doctor",
        "package",
        "real-upstream"
      ],
